  "title": "Site QS Engineer (Electrical)",
  "description": "<p><strong>About Company:</strong><br>\nOur client has been established since 1903 and their headquarters is in Osaka city. Their focus has been in building service engineering and installation provider for various sectors such as electrical, air conditioning and sanitary environments.<br>\n<br>\n<strong>Job Description:</strong><br>\n- To assist Manager to handle general contracts and various tender documents<br>\n- Able to provide budget cost or estimates as per instruction<br>\n- Liaise with suppliers for their products and services presentation<br>\n- Able to look for solution regarding any technical problems during tender<br>\n- Able to communicate with other departments in dealing with various documents and issue<br>\n- Coordinate with the supplier/contractor regarding follow up on bills and quantities<br>\n- To evaluate and check on market unit rates monthly/quarterly for material and labour cost<br>\n- To hand over all tender document and costing to project team once the tender is awarded<br>\n- To attend site show round for those tender that we are interested<br>\n- Reply tender clarification, preparation for tender interview and presentation<br>\n<br>\n<strong>Job Requirements:</strong><br>\n- Diploma in M&amp;E / Mechanical Engineering<br>\n- Min 3 years of relevant experience in M&amp;E Subcontractor environment<br>\n<br>\n<strong>Compensation:</strong><br>\n- Office location: Central; Site location: Bedok<br>\n- Working hours: Monday - Friday 8am to 4.45pm / 8.30am to 5.15pm<br>\n- Variable bonus and allowances</p>",
